# SandboxApp Architecture

## Overview

SandboxApp is a showcase that exercises every PigeonLib capability through small,
single-responsibility ECS systems that communicate only via components and events. The engine
systems (CameraSystem, ConfigLoaderSystem, InputSystem, Renderer2DSystem, ResourceManagerSystem,
SpriteAnimationSystem, SpriteRenderSystem, UIControlSystem, UIEventSystem, UIRenderSystem) are
registered by `Application::Init`. The sandbox
registers only the systems below; execution order is derived automatically from each system's
`DeclareAccess()`, so registration order is irrelevant.

## System Registration

```
pg::CreateApplication()  [Sandbox2D.cpp]
  ├── Sandbox::Create()                       (delegates to pg::Application::Create())
  └── World::RegisterSystem(...) for:
        sbx::ConfigLoaderSystem        Assets/App/Config.json -> SandboxConfigSingletonComponent
        sbx::TransformResolveSystem    app transform requests -> ResolvedTransformRequest (engine type)
        sbx::SceneSetupSystem          2D camera + sprite + animated character + labels + 3D camera + spinning model + 3D-output display sprite + transform requests + LoadLayoutEvent (once)
        sbx::ModelSpinSystem           ModelSpinComponent + time -> ModelSpinTransformRequest (spins the 3D model about Y)
        sbx::CameraControlSystem       held WASD + scroll + camera -> SetCameraRequest (engine type)
        sbx::CharacterControlSystem    held arrows -> CharacterTransformRequest (move) + SetSpriteAnimationRequest (facing/play)
        sbx::QuadSpawnSystem           seeds demo quads (+ spawn transform requests); spawns on SPACE
        sbx::QuadAnimationSystem       SpinComponent + time -> QuadComponent colour + AnimationTransformRequest
        sbx::LifetimeSystem            counts down LifetimeComponent; deferred-destroys expired
        sbx::QuadRenderSystem          QuadComponent + WorldTransform  -> DrawQuadInFrameEvent
        sbx::TextRenderSystem          LabelComponent + WorldTransform  -> DrawStringInFrameEvent

      Engine sprite systems (registered by Application::Init) consume the data the sandbox sets:
        pg::SpriteAnimationSystem      SetSpriteAnimationRequest + time -> SpriteComponent UVs (via pg::SpriteSheet)
        pg::SpriteRenderSystem         SpriteComponent + WorldTransform -> DrawSpriteInFrameEvent
        sbx::InputReadoutSystem        InputState         -> readout LabelComponent text
        sbx::UIButtonVisualSystem      hover/click        -> UIUpdateImageUUID (button image)
        sbx::UIButtonSystem            release            -> UIUpdateEnable (toggle panel)
        sbx::UICloseSystem             release            -> UIDestroy (dismiss element)
        sbx::UIStatusSystem            spawn count        -> UIUpdateText (status label)
        sbx::DialogueDemoSystem        ImGui "Dialogue" panel; typewriter text -> UIUpdateTextReveal (dialogue label)
        sbx::DebugPanelSystem          ImGui panel; owns DebugControlsSingletonComponent
        sbx::AudioDemoSystem           S/M/P keys -> Play/Stop/Pause/Resume audio requests; owns AudioDemoState
        sbx::AudioDebugPanelSystem     ImGui "Audio" panel; volume sliders -> SetAudioVolumeRequest
        sbx::WindowDebugPanelSystem    ImGui "Window" panel; resolution preset + mode -> SetWindowResolutionRequest
        sbx::SaveDataDebugPanelSystem  ImGui "Save Data" panel; slot list + JSON editor -> SetSaveDataRequest
```

## Boot Sequence

```
Frame 1
  engine ConfigLoaderSystem   -> EngineConfigSingletonComponent  (deferred)
  engine ResourceManagerSystem-> ResourceMapSingletonComponent   (deferred)
  sbx::ConfigLoaderSystem     -> SandboxConfigSingletonComponent (deferred)
  the lazy-singleton systems (QuadSpawn, UIButtonVisual, UIStatus, DebugPanel) create their
    state singletons; every other sandbox system guards on missing inputs and no-ops

Frame 2
  sbx::SceneSetupSystem  both config + resources present -> creates the scene camera, the static demo
                         sprite, the arrow-key animated character (sprite + 8x8 SpriteAnimationComponent +
                         CharacterTagComponent, starting idle), the title/instructions/input-readout
                         labels, emits LoadLayoutEvent, and creates SceneReadySingletonComponent (its
                         run-once guard)
  sbx::QuadSpawnSystem   config present, spawner absent -> seeds the persistent demo quads and
                         creates SpawnerSingletonComponent

Frame 3+  (steady state)
  engine UIControlSystem loads Data/Assets/App/UI/SandboxUI.json (from LoadLayoutEvent)
  the render bridges, animation, input, and UI interaction systems run every frame (below)
```

## Steady-State Data Flow

```
Input (engine InputSystem -> InputStateSingletonComponent)
  ├── sbx::CameraControlSystem    held WASD + scroll + camera zoom/pos -> SetCameraRequest (engine type)
  │      └── engine CameraSystem  applies zoom + pans (CameraTransformRequest); resize aspect (viewport)
  ├── sbx::CharacterControlSystem held arrows + character pos -> CharacterTransformRequest (move) +
  │                               SetSpriteAnimationRequest (facing row + play/stop)
  ├── sbx::QuadSpawnSystem        SPACE -> QuadComponent + SpinComponent + LifetimeComponent
  └── sbx::InputReadoutSystem     mouse/keys/scroll -> readout LabelComponent text

Transforms (ADR 0003, two-tier resolve)
  app movers emit per-mover requests:
    SpinComponent --(sbx::QuadAnimationSystem)--> AnimationTransformRequest (position + rotation)
    held arrows --(sbx::CharacterControlSystem)--> CharacterTransformRequest (character position)
    sbx::QuadSpawnSystem / sbx::SceneSetupSystem --> spawn / scene transform requests (initial P/R/S/Bounds)
  sbx::TransformResolveSystem aggregates all app requests --> one pg::ResolvedTransformRequest per entity
        └── engine TransformResolveSystem (+ camera pan request) writes Position/Rotation/Scale/LocalBounds
              └── engine TransformComposeSystem --> WorldTransformComponent (matrix + world-Y sort key)

World-space rendering
  QuadComponent   + WorldTransform --(sbx::QuadRenderSystem)--> DrawQuadInFrameEvent
  SetSpriteAnimationRequest + time --(engine pg::SpriteAnimationSystem)--> SpriteComponent sub-texture (sprite-sheet frame, via pg::SpriteSheet)
  SpriteComponent + WorldTransform --(engine pg::SpriteRenderSystem)--> DrawSpriteInFrameEvent
  LabelComponent  + WorldTransform --(sbx::TextRenderSystem, via ResourceMap font)--> DrawStringInFrameEvent
        └── engine Renderer2DSystem Y-sorts world draws (lower Y behind), draws UI on top, into GPU draw calls
  LifetimeComponent --(sbx::LifetimeSystem)--> deferred entity destroy when expired

3D rendering (ADR 0007; engine Renderer3DSystem)
  SceneSetupSystem authors a PerspectiveCameraComponent (looking at the origin), a model entity
    (ModelComponent + ModelSpinComponent, no Quad/Sprite so it is 3D-only), and a 2D display sprite
    textured with the 3D render target.
  ModelSpinComponent + time --(sbx::ModelSpinSystem)--> ModelSpinTransformRequest (Y-axis spin)
        └── aggregated by sbx::TransformResolveSystem -> resolved request -> Position/Rotation -> WorldTransform
  ModelComponent + WorldTransform + PerspectiveCameraComponent --(engine Renderer3DSystem)--> the model is
    drawn (depth-tested, flat unlit) into the offscreen render target before the 2D pass; its colour
    buffer is registered as a texture, which the display SpriteComponent samples in the 2D world pass.

UI (engine UIControlSystem + UIEventSystem + UIRenderSystem)
  UIEventSystem hit-tests the mouse -> UIOnClick / UIOnHover / UIOnRelease one-frame components
  ├── sbx::UIButtonVisualSystem  hover/click -> UIUpdateImageUUIDOneFrameComponent (button image)
  ├── sbx::UIButtonSystem        release on toggle button -> UIUpdateEnableOneFrameComponent (panel)
  ├── sbx::UICloseSystem         release on close button  -> UIDestroyOneFrameComponent (target)
  ├── sbx::UIStatusSystem        SpawnerSingletonComponent count -> UIUpdateTextOneFrameComponent
  └── sbx::DialogueDemoSystem    ImGui-edited line, revealed over time -> UIUpdateTextRevealOneFrameComponent
                                 (fixed-size word-wrapped dialogue label; re-reveals when the text is edited)
        └── engine UIControlSystem applies the UIUpdate*/UIDestroy components to BaseComponent /
            ImageComponent / TextComponent; UIRenderSystem then emits DrawUIQuad/DrawUIString events

ImGui
  sbx::DebugPanelSystem  slider -> DebugControlsSingletonComponent.m_AnimationSpeed
        └── read by sbx::QuadAnimationSystem to scale animation speed

Audio (engine AudioVolumeSystem + AudioPlaybackSystem)
  sbx::AudioDemoSystem        S -> one-shot sound voice; M -> toggle looping music; P -> pause/resume music
        └── emits Play/Stop/Pause/ResumeAudioRequest consumed by engine AudioPlaybackSystem
  sbx::AudioDebugPanelSystem  master/sound/music sliders -> SetAudioVolumeRequest
        └── engine AudioVolumeSystem writes AudioVolumeSingletonComponent; AudioPlaybackSystem applies it to voices

Window (engine WindowConfigSystem)
  sbx::WindowDebugPanelSystem  resolution preset dropdown + windowed/fullscreen radio + Apply -> SetWindowResolutionRequest
        └── engine WindowConfigSystem updates WindowConfigSingletonComponent, applies it to the live Window
            (windowed ↔ borderless fullscreen), and persists windowWidth/Height/Mode to <savedataPath>/Config.json

Save Data (engine SaveDataSystem)
  sbx::SaveDataDebugPanelSystem  slot list (from SaveDataSingletonComponent) + JSON text editor;
                                 Save -> SetSaveDataRequest (slot UUID + parsed JSON); Load refreshes the editor
        └── engine SaveDataSystem updates the slot in SaveDataSingletonComponent and rewrites
            <savedataPath>/SaveSlots/<uuid>.json
```

## Key Files

| File | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `Code/SandboxApp/Sandbox2D.cpp` | Entry point — CreateApplication() and sandbox system registration |
| `Code/SandboxApp/Sandbox/*System.cpp` | One focused system per file (see Documentation/ModuleInfo/SandboxApp) |
| `Code/SandboxApp/Sandbox/*Component.h` | Pure-data components and state singletons |
| `Code/SandboxApp/Sandbox/UIElementHelpers.*` | Shared sandbox helpers: find a UI element by UUID; UI event predicates |
| `Data/Assets/App/Config.json` | UUID references for fonts, textures, the 3D model, the UI layout, and targeted UI elements |
| `Data/Assets/App/UI/SandboxUI.json` | Root UI layout: toggle button + a dismissible panel (status text, note, close button) |
